
This directory contains the source code for an example
program that uses the libtelos to parse Telos Frames.
The library file libtelos.(a|dll|lib) can be found in
$CB_HOME/<arch>/lib
The program has an interactive mode which allows you
to select between a few test operations.

It should be possible to build this example program with any
C compiler (e.g., gcc or Microsoft Visual C++).

Compiler flags:
 - Solaris: -I$(CB_HOME)/include -DSOLARIS
 - Linux: -I$(CB_HOME)/include -DLINUX
 - Windows: -nologo -MT -W3 -GX -O2 -I$(CB_HOME)/include -D "WIN32" -D "NDEBUG" -D "_CONSOLE" -D "_MBCS" -Fo".\\" /Fd".\\" -c

Linker flags:
 - Solaris: -L$(CB_HOME)/sun4/lib -ltelos
 - Linux: -L$(CB_HOME)/linux/lib -ltelos
 - Windows: kernel32.lib user32.lib wsock32.lib $(CB_HOME)/windows/lib/libtelos.lib \
      -nologo -subsystem:console -incremental:no -machine:I386

For Windows, you have to make sure that the dynamic library libtelos.dll
is found when you execute the example application.

